  description: "concurrent.futures.CancelledError class identity checks in cfexceptions190 namespace â€” CancelledError.__name__=='CancelledError' (len=14: 'Cancelled'=9+'Error'=5=14; raised when a future is cancelled before completing); CancelledError.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24: 'concurrent'=10+'.'=1+'futures'=7+'.'=1+'_base'=5=24; defined in the private _base submodule alongside Future and Executor); CancelledError.__bases__[0].__name__=='Error' (len=5; inherits from the private Error base class in concurrent.futures._base, not from builtins directly); CancelledError.__module__ (24) >> TimeoutError.__module__ (8) â€” TimeoutError is a builtin while CancelledError is package-local; verified with Python 3.14.3"
